  "section_name": "Risk Analysis",
  "text": "Financial leverage and liquidity present moderate risk for Adobe. As of Q4 2025, the company carries total debt of $6,648,000,000 against stockholders' equity of $11,623,000,000, resulting in a debt-to-equity ratio of 0.57 (K009, C049, C047). Net debt stands at $1,217,000,000 after accounting for cash and equivalents of $5,431,000,000 (K010, C048). More notably, the current ratio at Q4 2025 is approximately 1.00, with current assets of $10,163,000,000 against current liabilities of $10,200,000,000 (K008, C051, C052). This tight liquidity position suggests limited short-term financial flexibility, though the company maintains positive net cash positioning overall.",
